- About North?
- The guy who always come play games at your cafe.

263
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,110
- Um.
- His name is North?

264
00:17:38,570 --> 00:17:40,160
Um his name is North.

265
00:17:40,570 --> 00:17:42,040
Why do you ask?

266
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:45,940
Nothing.
t's just that I heard him talking to his friend yesterday.

267
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:48,250
Why?

268
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,840
It went right through your heart huh?

269
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:59,070
To be honest, he's actually the opposite of you.

270
00:17:59,550 --> 00:18:02,680
From what I heard, his dad died.

271
00:18:02,970 --> 00:18:05,220
he lives with his mom and his aunt.

272
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:08,410
Their family is not well off.

273
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,840
He has to do extra jobs.

274
00:18:12,290 --> 00:18:13,900
Isn't he like in grade 10 only?

275
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:17,430
He's been working since junior high.

276
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:21,370
And what's he like?

277
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,130
He's a pretty chill guy.

278
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:27,440
People can be themselves around him.

279
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:30,820
- He's really like that?
- Yeah.

280
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,070
North is very lively.

281
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:42,070
- Follow me.
- On my way.

282
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:44,580
- Fire. Fire.
- I got one down.

283
00:18:44,610 --> 00:18:45,480
Nice.

284
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,780
- I got it.
- Nice.

285
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:50,240
- Alright. Alright.
- Hey. Hey. Shh.

286
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,600
My mom. My mom.

287
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:55,670
Hello, mom?

288
00:18:55,670 --> 00:18:56,870
Have you eaten, North?

289
00:18:56,930 --> 00:18:58,130
I did.

290
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:59,860
What about you?

291
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,640
I also did.

292
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:02,880
Oh mom.

293
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:04,950
I will spend a night at my friend's today.

294
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:05,910
Why?

295
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:07,990
We will work on a group project.

296
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:11,640
Ok. Take care then.

297
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:14,360
Sure mom. Don't miss me though.

298
00:19:14,430 --> 00:19:15,480
Sure~

299
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:18,090
Sure mom.

300
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:20,860
- Go in.
- North.

301
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:23,410
Are you sure lying to your mom like that?

302
00:19:24,710 --> 00:19:26,930
Yeah I'm gonna work on my group project.

303
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:29,550
But our project is done.

304
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:33,690
Cause I wanna play games.
I can't stop playing here.

305
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,470
Up to you then.

306
00:19:35,630 --> 00:19:38,580
- North.
- Why are you calling me? Just walk there.

307
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:40,440
- North!
- Oh mom!

308
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,800
You said you're working on a group project?

309
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:44,970
Tae. Ball.

310
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,550
Yes?

311
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:49,090
I already called your parents to come pick you guys up.

312
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:50,800
They will be here soon.

313
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,360
Thank you.

314
00:19:54,910 --> 00:19:57,940
- And for you, come here.
- Ow. Mom.

315
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,170
- Come here.
- Mom. Mom.

316
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:03,100
You're lying to me now?

317
00:20:03,150 --> 00:20:06,050
I'm fine with you addicted to playing games,

318
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:09,420
- But this is too much. Not going home. People do worry, you know?
- Ow. Mom.

319
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:11,150
Don't fool around like this.

320
00:20:11,330 --> 00:20:13,340
Ow. Mom.

321
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:16,400
- You're embarrassing me.
- I'm not embarrassed.

322
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:19,280
You should be.

323
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:20,980
I'm sorry.

324
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:23,740
I was wrong.

325
00:20:24,270 --> 00:20:25,860
Don't say sorry now.

326
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:30,300
You're twisting my ears like this.

327
00:20:30,910 --> 00:20:34,210
Are you hurt? i do care about you.

328
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:39,480
Let's go find something yummy to eat, shall we?
So you might be in a better mood.

329
00:20:40,860 --> 00:20:42,030
Please mom.

330
00:20:43,230 --> 00:20:44,670
Eat something yummy.

331
00:20:44,930 --> 00:20:46,960
So you can be in a better mood, shall we?

332
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,580
Hey you're smiling now.

333
00:20:51,630 --> 00:20:54,430
- Let's go eat.
- Um. Fine.

334
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:56,660
- Something yummy, okay? Let's go.
- Yeah.

335
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:59,240
Stop being mad at me, yeah?

336
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:01,810
- Wait mom.
- What?

337
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:03,690
I forgot my bag.

338
00:21:04,730 --> 00:21:05,990
Hurry and go get it.

339
00:21:06,710 --> 00:21:07,980
Ok mom.

340
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,160
I'll be right back.

341
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:10,480
Hey guys.

342
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:11,990
See you.

343
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:14,390
I will go deal my mom first.

344
00:21:14,450 --> 00:21:15,770
Good luck.

345
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:18,780
- I'm back.
- Come on. Hurry up.

346
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:20,370
Let's go eat.

347
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:21,960
Which restaurant shall we go?

348
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:24,440
- The meatball is also good.
- is it?

349
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,480
- It is.
- Sure.

350
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:30,440
And what kind of a person is he?

351
00:21:31,070 --> 00:21:32,780
He's a pretty chill guy.

352
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,960
People can be themselves around him.

353
00:21:42,850 --> 00:21:45,010
Right. Right. Done!

354
00:21:45,090 --> 00:21:48,090
There're so many ways dude.
Hey hey. I found one.

355
00:21:48,210 --> 00:21:49,260
Oh.

356
00:21:49,290 --> 00:21:53,690
Here. Here. Behind me. Go in.
Behind me.

357
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,330
Be careful. Behind you!

358
00:21:55,690 --> 00:21:57,100
Hey.

359
00:21:58,910 --> 00:22:00,550
Dude. I'm hungry.

360
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,560
I will go use the restroom. Be right back.

361
00:22:22,470 --> 00:22:24,610
I'm back.

362
00:22:29,550 --> 00:22:30,980
Whose snacks are these?

363
00:22:31,940 --> 00:22:34,350
If no one claims it, it will be mine now.

364
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,260
I'm back. Wait a minute.

365
00:22:39,830 --> 00:22:42,470
Yeah just like that. I got you.

366
00:22:42,690 --> 00:22:45,610
I'm going in! There!
Sorry mate.

367
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:49,590
Come on.

368
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:52,160
Feels like someone is following behind me.

369
00:22:55,900 --> 00:22:59,130
Hey how can you jump and shoot me?
What are you? A bird?

370
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:28,740
Thank you.

371
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,530
Please P'James.

372
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,920
I already gave you a few minutes.

373
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,370
A bit more please.

374
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,770
How long did you play just now?

375
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,660
- 2 hours.
- And you want more?

376
00:23:43,950 --> 00:23:46,110
2 more.

377
00:23:46,270 --> 00:23:48,610
What a way for me to make so much profits.

378
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:50,540
Please. I don't normally ask you this.

379
00:23:50,540 --> 00:23:53,850
I just gave you some.
Fine. I'll give you 2 more.

380
00:23:53,930 --> 00:23:56,000
- 2 hours?
- 2 minutes.

381
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:58,280
I cannot even log into the game just 2 mins.

382
00:24:14,310 --> 00:24:15,480
What!?

383
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:19,950
Can I ask you something?

384
00:24:21,790 --> 00:24:22,780
If...

385
00:24:25,420 --> 00:24:26,720
If...

386
00:24:27,830 --> 00:24:29,200
What!?

387
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,210
Do you think...

388
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:37,420
is it weird if I like someone even that person has never done anything for me?

389
00:24:37,550 --> 00:24:39,280
What are you actually asking?

390
00:24:39,490 --> 00:24:42,380
And what do you think?
What do people do if they like someone?

391
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:44,790
Are they gonna take bullets for each other like the movies?

392
00:24:44,790 --> 00:24:45,690
Bang. Bang.

393
00:24:47,810 --> 00:24:49,140
I don't know.

394
00:24:49,710 --> 00:24:53,360
It's not weird.
You can just see someone and fall for them too.

395
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:55,530
Why? Who are you having crush on?

396
00:24:55,940 --> 00:24:58,730
Yeah...a person like you, Jo?

397
00:24:59,260 --> 00:25:01,560
- Who is it?
- How am I supposed to know?

398
00:25:05,131 --> 00:25:06,540
He's a Nong.
(Thais use Nong to call someone younger)

399
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,160
Nong?

400
00:25:10,390 --> 00:25:11,820
North!?

401
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:15,420
Yeah.

402
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:18,110
I knew it!

403
00:25:18,170 --> 00:25:19,970
You always check him out.

404
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:23,180
And you've been coming to my cafe a lot too.

405
00:25:23,380 --> 00:25:26,000
You really like him for real? Why though?

406
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,800
I'm not sure why either.

407
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:34,170
That's why I ask whether it's possible for someone to like a person that has never done anything to you?

408
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:38,220
But it's not totally true that he's never done anything to me.

409
00:25:39,260 --> 00:25:43,680
He's the reason why I wanna change myself.

410
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:47,750
I wanna see him smile.

411
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:50,880
I don't wanna see him being cute with anyone else.

412
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:55,350
I don't think you just like him, but you're obsessed with him.

413
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:03,540
Let me take care of this for you.

414
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:06,480
Are you gonna make it work or worse?

415
00:26:06,610 --> 00:26:07,960
We're rooting for you.

416
00:26:13,020 --> 00:26:14,010
What are you doing?

417
00:26:15,020 --> 00:26:16,700
Trust me.

418
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:19,980
- What are you gonna do? Tell me first.
- Just stay still.

419
00:26:27,490 --> 00:26:29,710
- North.
- Yes, P'?

420
00:26:29,850 --> 00:26:31,880
- I have question.
- What is it?

421
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:36,510
My friend really likes you.

422
00:26:37,050 --> 00:26:39,110
He actually wanna tell you himself,

423
00:26:39,350 --> 00:26:41,790
but I think I should ask you first.

424
00:26:42,460 --> 00:26:44,360
Whether you're dating someone?

425
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,240
I am actually.

426
00:26:53,030 --> 00:26:54,500
Oh really?

427
00:26:54,570 --> 00:26:55,360
Um.

428
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:57,670
How come I don't know?

429
00:26:57,820 --> 00:26:59,960
Last time, you said you're not dating anyone.

430
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,980
I was trying to pursue her back then.

431
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:04,320
We just made it official a few days ago.

432
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:06,190
I'm sorry.

433
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,020
But...

434
00:27:10,660 --> 00:27:12,640
my friend really likes you...like a lot.

435
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,910
Don't you wanna try talking? Just a little?

436
00:27:15,530 --> 00:27:16,560
Ugh.

437
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:19,030
I told you. I'm already seeing someone.

438
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:22,050
If I agree to do that, that means I'll be cheating.

439
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:23,540
Um.

440
00:27:24,930 --> 00:27:27,150
but my friend really likes you, North.

441
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:31,230
Wrong timing I guess.

442
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,790
- I'm sorry bro.
- Um.

443
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:44,710
- You'll find soon.
- Run. Run.

444
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:46,670
- You need to use your pinky.
- Pinky finger?

445
00:27:46,810 --> 00:27:48,670
It looks more professional.

446
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,610
- Oh it's more professional?
- Yeah.

447
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:53,160
- Run. Run.
- Using your thumb doesn't look professional.

448
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:55,790
- This?
- Here. Found it.

449
00:27:57,020 --> 00:27:59,040
- Go in.
- Okay. Oh.

450
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:00,530
Why?

451
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:03,250
Run. Run. Like that.

452
00:28:05,290 --> 00:28:06,710
So?

453
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:09,640
He's always here playing games with his girl everyday.

454
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:11,530
You're sitting there like a sad dog.

455
00:28:11,540 --> 00:28:14,580
I give you that.
Seeing him with his girlfriend everyday.

456
00:28:16,910 --> 00:28:19,240
I wanna see him. Not his girlfriend.

457
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:22,280
You're always here looking at him for months.

458
00:28:23,530 --> 00:28:24,770
Does he have any idea that...

459
00:28:25,210 --> 00:28:28,000
there's someone
so obsessed with his smile like this?

460
00:28:28,010 --> 00:28:31,950
He can do anything just to see his smile. Wow.

461
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:34,050
So romantic.

462
00:28:35,670 --> 00:28:38,000
I thought I should be fine at first,

463
00:28:38,620 --> 00:28:40,550
but how come it hurts a little.

464
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:50,360
When you love someone,

465
00:28:50,550 --> 00:28:53,200
you need to spare your feelings.
It can be hurtful too, Jo.

466
00:28:54,230 --> 00:28:56,740
But for a person who's never been in love with anyone,

467
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:58,000
I know...

468
00:28:58,180 --> 00:28:59,530
that it must be difficult.

469
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,260
Damn.

470
00:29:02,660 --> 00:29:04,650
I feel bad for you.

471
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,050
Even...

472
00:29:06,540 --> 00:29:08,450
there's someone for you to love,

473
00:29:08,690 --> 00:29:09,880
but...

474
00:29:10,630 --> 00:29:13,420
you don't even have the chance to at least try.

475
00:29:14,930 --> 00:29:17,800
He rejects you all the way,

476
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:21,310
But that's good.
At least you know that he's faithful to his partner.

477
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:22,890
Um.

478
00:29:24,310 --> 00:29:25,680
What are you gonna do now?

479
00:29:26,020 --> 00:29:27,110
Giving up?

480
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:28,550
I think...

481
00:29:29,150 --> 00:29:31,720
it's less likely that he'll breakup with his girl soon.

482
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,480
I think so too.

483
00:29:34,170 --> 00:29:36,150
I probably won't be able to see him again.

484
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,230
- I ask my dad to work too.
- Huh?

485
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:42,590
I get the not seeing him part.

486
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,220
But you're gonna work!?

487
00:29:44,380 --> 00:29:46,330
Are you sure?

488
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:48,720
Um.

489
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:50,880
It's because of him.

490
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:54,600
I wanna try doing something meaningful too.

491
00:29:55,370 --> 00:29:57,410
What was your dad reaction?

492
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,170
He was surprised.

493
00:29:59,310 --> 00:30:02,600
But he said If I take it seriously,
he will let me live with my uncle in LA.

494
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:03,750
LA?

495
00:30:03,910 --> 00:30:05,880
And...are you going?

496
00:30:06,810 --> 00:30:07,920
Um.

497
00:30:16,290 --> 00:30:18,200
I'll probably go there for a year.

498
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:20,840
Then come back for university here.

499
00:30:22,830 --> 00:30:25,220
It's the only way that I can move on from him.

500
00:30:33,380 --> 00:30:34,520
Go. Go.

501
00:30:36,130 --> 00:30:37,220
Nice. Oh.

502
00:30:37,490 --> 00:30:38,620
What?

503
00:30:39,330 --> 00:30:40,790
P'James.

504
00:31:05,170 --> 00:31:06,310
P'James.

505
00:31:06,690 --> 00:31:08,610
Hey who allow you to walk in?

506
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,610
The sign says staff only.

507
00:31:10,670 --> 00:31:12,260
I'm not an outsider.

508
00:31:12,290 --> 00:31:14,850
This is like my second home already.

509
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:16,850
What do you need?

510
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,680
Hey. You're playing guitar?

511
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:21,100
Um.

512
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,390
I'm actually practicing it.

513
00:31:23,500 --> 00:31:24,310
Really?

514
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:26,100
- You wanna try?
- Sure.

515
00:31:28,490 --> 00:31:30,080
What song do you wanna play?

516
00:31:31,060 --> 00:31:32,240
Umm...

517
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:35,760
I'm into country songs about life lately.

518
00:31:36,710 --> 00:31:37,990
You are?

519
00:31:38,510 --> 00:31:39,300
Um.

520
00:31:40,860 --> 00:31:42,990
Kinda tired and feeling hopeless.

521
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:45,940
So I need to listen to songs that inspire me.

522
00:31:46,620 --> 00:31:49,000
Also, I have a problem with my girlfriend.

523
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:51,570
About what? Tell me.

524
00:31:52,190 --> 00:31:53,590
I don't know.

525
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:57,120
I've been dating her for 2 months already.

526
00:31:58,470 --> 00:32:01,270
But seems like she's never been happy being with me.

527
00:32:04,940 --> 00:32:06,500
She's tired after class sometimes,

528
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:07,930
and she doesn't wanna see me.

529
00:32:09,370 --> 00:32:11,620
I understand that she's tired,

530
00:32:11,950 --> 00:32:12,840
but....

531
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,040
I wanna be someone who helps with her tiredness.

532
00:32:18,130 --> 00:32:19,710
So you feel like...

533
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,270
you're useless to her?

534
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:24,950
I guess so.

535
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:28,670
If I date someone, I wanna be like a sanctuary for them.

536
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:31,640
Being together
and improving each other's lives.

537
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:32,180
Um.

538
00:32:32,380 --> 00:32:34,840
I wanna help her no matter what happens,

539
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:37,140
But...

540
00:32:38,310 --> 00:32:40,580
I can't help her with anything.
Even if...

541
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,340
I tried so hard already.

542
00:32:48,020 --> 00:32:49,460
So I think...

543
00:32:50,340 --> 00:32:54,200
It would be nice if you're with someone
who really wants you to be in their lives.

544
00:32:58,060 --> 00:32:58,820
Hey.

545
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,920
Why am I telling you all those?

546
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:02,880
I actually wanted you to fix the computer.

547
00:33:02,970 --> 00:33:04,080
The screen is blacked out.

548
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:07,010
- Um. You go wait outside. I'll be there in a sec.
- Hurry up please.

549
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:08,540
- Um.
- My hour is running.

550
00:33:08,870 --> 00:33:10,220
Right. I'll do it.

551
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,130
- i'm losing my hour here.
- Go.

552
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:18,060
- Still not coming?
- You go ahead.

553
00:33:19,270 --> 00:33:21,360
- Hurry up, P'.
- Yeah.

554
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:29,230
You heard that right?

555
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,550
Um.

556
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:40,850
You said you wanna move on.

557
00:33:41,990 --> 00:33:44,120
But heard something like that...

558
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,070
are you sure you can?

559
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:48,720
Someone he wants to be with...

560
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:51,320
Someone who will improve each other's lives...

561
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:54,160
That's you.

562
00:33:56,450 --> 00:33:57,850
But what can I do?

563
00:33:58,290 --> 00:33:59,810
I can't do anything.

564
00:34:02,430 --> 00:34:04,120
Should you just steal him from her?

565
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,700
- Why would I do that for?
- Hey.

566
00:34:07,180 --> 00:34:08,400
If I do that,

567
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,760
he will be the one who disappoints the most.

568
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,340
I don't want to take his smiles away.

569
00:34:16,640 --> 00:34:18,040
What a good guy.

570
00:34:24,350 --> 00:34:26,510
You're leaving tomorrow?

571
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:28,190
Um.

572
00:34:29,170 --> 00:34:30,540
Call us sometimes.

573
00:34:34,410 --> 00:34:36,010
Maybe this is for the best,

574
00:34:37,170 --> 00:34:39,040
taking time to heal yourself.

575
00:34:39,250 --> 00:34:42,090
If you live here, you wouldn't be able to move on.

576
00:34:42,300 --> 00:34:43,900
True.

577
00:34:44,100 --> 00:34:46,480
I think this is enough already for this one.

578
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:51,140
I wanted you to wait for him actually,
but I don't think you should anymore.

579
00:34:54,570 --> 00:34:56,380
I also don't wanna wait anymore.

580
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:58,790
It hurts.

581
00:35:27,180 --> 00:35:29,370
James, please look after him.

582
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,160
Yeah.

583
00:35:31,700 --> 00:35:33,290
I will.

584
00:35:41,210 --> 00:35:43,560
- Oh. That was easy.
- Here. Here. There's one more.

585
00:35:44,180 --> 00:35:46,080
- Same spot.
- Here?

586
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:48,840
So that was from someone who said he wants to move on.

587
00:35:48,860 --> 00:35:49,900
Why isn't he running?

588
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:51,410
Jump.

589
00:35:57,490 --> 00:35:58,390
Uncle.

590
00:35:58,430 --> 00:36:00,850
- Hmm?
- The uncle doesn't come anymore?

591
00:36:00,850 --> 00:36:02,500
Yeah, he doesn't come anymore.

592
00:36:02,550 --> 00:36:05,060
You make it too sweet for him.

593
00:36:05,270 --> 00:36:07,390
It's not. I always taste it first.

594
00:36:07,700 --> 00:36:10,760
Or he switched to buy from some other places?

595
00:36:11,430 --> 00:36:15,280
Yeah, just hurry, close up, and go to school already.

596
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:16,670
Come on. Hurry up.

597
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:19,600
There. There. Pack it all up over there.

598
00:36:26,910 --> 00:36:28,300
- P'James.
- Um?

599
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:30,690
Same one for 2 hours.

600
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:31,900
Ok same table.

601
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:53,490
Thank you.

602
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,800
And how's everything with your girlfriend?

603
00:37:10,220 --> 00:37:11,370
Good.

604
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:13,000
We're together for almost a year now.

605
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:13,920
Really?

606
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:17,550
Last time you said she doesn't wanna be with you?

607
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:18,570
Well...

608
00:37:18,620 --> 00:37:20,040
now we're okay.

609
00:37:20,850 --> 00:37:21,970
That's good.

610
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,540
- I have to go.
- Um.

611
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:27,610
- Oh, P'James.
- Hmm?

612
00:37:28,160 --> 00:37:29,720
You know...

613
00:37:30,410 --> 00:37:33,220
there's is this one guy who always gives me snacks.

614
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:36,440
Do you know who is this?

615
00:37:37,090 --> 00:37:37,960
Does he....?

616
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,410
still come around?

617
00:37:41,150 --> 00:37:42,520
Why do you ask?

618
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:45,080
I haven't seen him for so long already.

619
00:37:45,230 --> 00:37:46,880
When I stay here really late,

620
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:49,230
he's always hang around with me.

621
00:37:52,420 --> 00:37:54,460
Nothing...I just...

622
00:37:54,870 --> 00:37:56,790
wanna give him back some snacks too.

623
00:37:56,790 --> 00:37:58,700
Cause he's been giving me so often.

624
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:02,650
I will tell him for you if I see him.

625
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:05,300
- Sure. I'm really gonna go now.
- Um.

626
00:38:06,290 --> 00:38:08,020
I brought you some snacks too.

627
00:38:08,070 --> 00:38:09,690
That's mine though, but thanks.

628
00:38:14,510 --> 00:38:16,000
All done.

629
00:38:16,020 --> 00:38:16,870
Thank you.

630
00:38:18,290 --> 00:38:20,960
Oh hey uncle!
I haven't seen you for so long.

631
00:38:21,350 --> 00:38:23,550
My boss actually went to study abroad.

632
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:25,340
Boss?

633
00:38:25,940 --> 00:38:27,600
You normally buy for someone else?

634
00:38:27,650 --> 00:38:29,280
I thought you always buy it for yourself.

635
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:32,680
No, I always buy it for my young boss.

636
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:35,550
I can make less sweet soy milk now.

637
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:38,270
Yummy for sure.

638
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:41,000
I will give you free fried dumplings as usual.

639
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:43,140
Since you haven't been here for awhile.

640
00:38:43,290 --> 00:38:46,410
It's fine. This time is on me.

641
00:38:46,530 --> 00:38:49,580
Please tell your young boss 'Welcome home' for me.

642
00:38:49,690 --> 00:38:51,030
Sure.

643
00:38:52,450 --> 00:38:54,010
He told you that?

644
00:38:54,050 --> 00:38:54,890
Yes.

645
00:39:08,210 --> 00:39:09,850
You ran aways for a year,

646
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:12,760
but fall for him again because of a few fried dumplings?

647
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,530
I've been hearing the word 'wait' everyday.

648
00:39:15,640 --> 00:39:16,880
'When is he gonna come?'

649
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:19,260
My friend is so into it.

650
00:39:21,190 --> 00:39:25,050
Oh he was asking for you
when he came to my cafe too.

651
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:29,330
Why did you tell him that?

652
00:39:29,410 --> 00:39:30,540
Hey.

653
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:34,620
You didn't see anyone when you were in LA?

654
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:38,620
I couldn't do it.

655
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:41,020
I tried to open my mind,

656
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,150
but I always miss him.

657
00:39:44,290 --> 00:39:45,260
So...

658
00:39:45,730 --> 00:39:47,050
you went away for a year...

659
00:39:47,370 --> 00:39:48,760
but you cannot move on still?

660
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:50,270
If you're still like this...

661
00:39:50,900 --> 00:39:52,720
you will stuck with him your whole life.

662
00:39:55,740 --> 00:39:59,020
When I go to university and no longer see him,

663
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:00,550
will I be able move on from him?

664
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:02,920
You went to La, which is very far, you still cannot.

665
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,270
What do you think then?

666
00:40:05,300 --> 00:40:06,290
Yeah.

667
00:40:06,390 --> 00:40:07,680
Right.

668
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:15,390
Are you trying to kill me?

669
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:17,890
Oops. Sorry from the behind.

670
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:33,390
Shit!

671
00:40:33,770 --> 00:40:35,760
There's no one left here.

672
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:37,590
Am I gonna meet any ghosts here?

673
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:38,940
I have to go.

674
00:40:40,540 --> 00:40:42,230
Yeah see you.

675
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:46,150
Hey dude.

676
00:40:47,330 --> 00:40:49,030
I can continue playing now.

677
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,520
There's someone just walked in.

678
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:55,330
Let's play until the sunrise.

679
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:59,900
Yeah do it.

680
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:05,410
Come behind me.
I heard. I heard.

681
00:41:09,180 --> 00:41:11,260
What time is it now?

682
00:41:11,930 --> 00:41:12,750
Huh!?

683
00:41:13,160 --> 00:41:14,360
For real?

684
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:18,500
I have to go for real.
My mom will probably yell at me now.

685
00:41:25,060 --> 00:41:27,760
Thanks for hanging around with me.

686
00:41:29,550 --> 00:41:30,600
Gotta go.

687
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:32,930
You'll be here alone now.

688
00:41:49,690 --> 00:41:53,100
Please hang with me at night like you used to do it.
I'm scared of ghosts.

689
00:41:53,180 --> 00:41:56,820
It's like you're trying to mess with me,
when I'm trying to move on here.

690
00:41:57,140 --> 00:41:58,620
At the end...

691
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:01,030
I still cannot do it.

692
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:05,080
But when I got into meds faculty,

693
00:42:05,230 --> 00:42:07,660
I met Hill, Fah, and Arthit.

694
00:42:08,220 --> 00:42:11,210
I decided not to see you again.

695
00:42:11,270 --> 00:42:12,560
Just live my life.

696
00:42:13,140 --> 00:42:14,390
Never care about anyone.

697
00:42:14,570 --> 00:42:17,600
Acted like a player. Never approached anyone first.

698
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:22,180
I thought I could move on from you.

699
00:42:22,470 --> 00:42:25,970
It's Trigonometry.
You asked me this during the class too. Memorize it.

700
00:42:26,700 --> 00:42:28,590
Jo. Have you heard of  the new?

701
00:42:28,700 --> 00:42:31,350
He got a scholarship to study in the US.

702
00:42:34,210 --> 00:42:36,560
Hey Jo. Where are you going?

703
00:42:39,540 --> 00:42:41,340
I know that you wanna move on from him.

704
00:42:41,510 --> 00:42:43,720
But today is his last orientation.

705
00:42:43,900 --> 00:42:45,550
Don't you wanna go see him a little?

706
00:42:45,710 --> 00:42:48,040
To at least congratulate him.

707
00:42:49,950 --> 00:42:53,430
After today, you might not get to see him ever again.

708
00:43:06,890 --> 00:43:09,210
We should break up.

709
00:43:14,700 --> 00:43:15,900
Good luck.

710
00:43:26,410 --> 00:43:27,380
James.

711
00:43:28,190 --> 00:43:29,820
He just got dumped.

712
00:43:30,370 --> 00:43:32,170
What happened?

713
00:43:33,260 --> 00:43:36,110
What should I do? I don't wanna see him cry.

714
00:43:36,620 --> 00:43:38,430
Go comfort him.

715
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:41,160
He doesn't even know me.

716
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:45,880
Then buy something for him.

717
00:43:46,060 --> 00:43:48,020
You can make him smile...maybe.

718
00:44:07,730 --> 00:44:10,260
Do you have any other dolls?

719
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:12,830
No, I sold it all. This is the only one left.

720
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:19,860
- I'll take this one then.
- THB250.

721
00:44:20,670 --> 00:44:22,990
I don't have any cash. Do you take credit card?

722
00:44:23,020 --> 00:44:24,750
I don't know how it use that.

723
00:44:26,340 --> 00:44:28,850
I will transfer to pay you then.

724
00:44:28,980 --> 00:44:30,340
I take cash only.

725
00:44:37,630 --> 00:44:39,770
I will pay with this then.

726
00:44:39,960 --> 00:44:42,250
Oh. It's too much.

727
00:44:42,310 --> 00:44:45,420
No, you can't do this. It's too expensive.

728
00:44:50,640 --> 00:44:53,380
Also...do you have any pen and paper?

729
00:44:53,630 --> 00:44:54,750
Yes.

730
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:56,780
Here.

731
00:45:03,060 --> 00:45:06,400
Err...your watch is too expensive son.

732
00:45:18,470 --> 00:45:19,130
Nong.

733
00:45:19,490 --> 00:45:22,340
Can you give this to that guy?

734
00:45:38,720 --> 00:45:40,370
Someone wants to give you this.

735
00:45:46,630 --> 00:45:49,150
Smile please :)

736
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:33,120
Why do you look so silly, huh?

737
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:35,270
Hey North.

738
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:39,070
What did Jah talk to you about?

739
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:40,780
Oh...

740
00:46:41,120 --> 00:46:43,880
- I just got dumped.
- Huh!?

741
00:46:44,100 --> 00:46:45,640
- How!?
- Like broke up?

742
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:47,420
- Hey.
- Are you okay?

743
00:46:47,780 --> 00:46:49,510
Forget it.

744
00:46:50,070 --> 00:46:51,300
Are you sure you're okay?

745
00:46:52,140 --> 00:46:53,210
You just got dumped.

746
00:46:53,380 --> 00:46:54,550
Her look.

747
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:56,780
It's cute, isn't it?

748
00:46:56,820 --> 00:46:59,240
Looking so silly.

749
00:46:59,260 --> 00:47:00,750
- Someone gave you this?
- Yeah.

750
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,090
It's so damn cute.

751
00:47:02,150 --> 00:47:03,100
Shit.

752
00:47:03,270 --> 00:47:04,580
But it actually looks like you.

753
00:47:04,690 --> 00:47:05,900
Suits you.

754
00:47:06,030 --> 00:47:09,290
- You said I look liks this duck?
- No. No.

755
00:47:09,390 --> 00:47:11,050
- Look at him.
- But it's cute.

756
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:12,210
Cute. Cute.

757
00:47:12,310 --> 00:47:13,680
- Let's go.
- See you.

758
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:15,100
Yeah.

759
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:46,370
I am smiling. Thank you.

760
00:48:12,510 --> 00:48:14,080
Where have you gone?

761
00:48:15,690 --> 00:48:17,400
Where are you now?

762
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:19,600
At a bar.

763
00:48:20,620 --> 00:48:21,930
Alone?

764
00:48:22,140 --> 00:48:23,030
Um.

765
00:48:25,230 --> 00:48:27,530
Where are you? I'll see you there.

766
00:48:52,290 --> 00:48:53,450
What's going on?

767
00:48:54,660 --> 00:48:56,320
Why are you so drunk like this?

768
00:48:57,520 --> 00:48:59,210
I don't know, Hill.

769
00:48:59,660 --> 00:49:01,000
I don't understand either.

770
00:49:13,910 --> 00:49:15,650
Why?

771
00:49:15,970 --> 00:49:18,160
- Why?
- Hey Jo.

772
00:49:18,270 --> 00:49:19,510
Calm down.

773
00:49:21,030 --> 00:49:23,320
I don't like the way I feel like this.

774
00:49:24,950 --> 00:49:27,480
I don't like myself for being like this.

775
00:49:28,650 --> 00:49:29,750
Hill.

776
00:49:30,980 --> 00:49:33,520
Do you ever have someone you want to be in your life,

777
00:49:34,110 --> 00:49:35,600
but you just can't?

778
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:40,530
You can give him everything,

779
00:49:41,480 --> 00:49:43,200
literally anything...

780
00:49:44,450 --> 00:49:46,240
just to see him smile.

781
00:49:48,070 --> 00:49:49,960
But why...

782
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:53,460
why can't I have him by my side?

783
00:50:03,520 --> 00:50:05,330
Dude...

784
00:50:06,400 --> 00:50:08,320
What if I say I have someone like that...

785
00:50:09,290 --> 00:50:11,160
are you gonna believe me?

786
00:50:29,740 --> 00:50:31,390
Easter?

787
00:50:34,690 --> 00:50:36,240
East means like where the sunrise.

788
00:50:36,770 --> 00:50:38,020
That's nice.

789
00:50:38,590 --> 00:50:40,480
North also means like in the north.

790
00:50:40,810 --> 00:50:43,310
Yeah.

791
00:50:46,350 --> 00:50:48,990
And he's going to America soon?

792
00:50:49,740 --> 00:50:51,220
Too bad.

793
00:50:51,550 --> 00:50:53,800
the fact that he's not seeing anyone anymore.

794
00:50:56,440 --> 00:50:57,600
Um.

795
00:50:59,250 --> 00:51:00,770
What about you?

796
00:51:00,960 --> 00:51:03,010
He probably hates you now.

797
00:51:06,610 --> 00:51:08,170
I think so.

798
00:51:08,980 --> 00:51:11,070
Not surprising if that happens.

799
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:13,890
I even hate myself.

800
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:19,820
God is not on our sides, Hill.

801
00:51:20,470 --> 00:51:21,880
What are you gonna do now?

802
00:51:22,380 --> 00:51:24,030
What can I do?

803
00:51:24,350 --> 00:51:25,590
But actually...

804
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:29,140
you've been waiting for him for so long too.

805
00:51:30,580 --> 00:51:31,840
How did you do it?

806
00:51:33,450 --> 00:51:35,620
It's nothing, Jo.

807
00:51:38,260 --> 00:51:40,590
I just can't move on from him.

808
00:51:41,450 --> 00:51:43,350
I'm stuck there.

809
00:51:44,280 --> 00:51:45,760
Not that different from you.

810
00:51:56,340 --> 00:51:58,900
Hill.

811
00:52:00,020 --> 00:52:01,610
When tomorrow comes,

812
00:52:04,540 --> 00:52:06,960
can you forget everything that happens today?

813
00:52:09,460 --> 00:52:11,330
Like everything.

814
00:52:12,850 --> 00:52:14,960
Including what I told you too.

815
00:52:17,020 --> 00:52:18,730
Why?

816
00:52:21,640 --> 00:52:23,680
I just don't wanna think about it anymore.

817
00:52:41,140 --> 00:52:42,340
Wow.

818
00:52:44,910 --> 00:52:47,190
Why are they this drunk?

819
00:52:48,310 --> 00:52:51,460
I actually asked Hill to look after Jo.

820
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:55,820
- And why did he end up like this?
- I don't know.

821
00:52:56,070 --> 00:52:57,540
I will go pay the bill.

822
00:52:57,900 --> 00:52:59,670
Let's take them home.

823
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:01,280
Yeah.

824
00:53:03,220 --> 00:53:04,750
Let's go. That's enough.

825
00:53:05,310 --> 00:53:06,520
Hill.

826
00:53:09,180 --> 00:53:12,270
Since that day, I cannot remember anything about Ter.

827
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:15,060
But Hill can remember everything.

828
00:53:16,130 --> 00:53:17,660
At the end...

829
00:53:18,130 --> 00:53:19,970
I couldn't move on from you.

830
00:53:20,600 --> 00:53:22,640
And then you got into a fight...

831
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:24,790
because of the new boyfriend of your ex.

832
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:32,270
I'm sorry.

833
00:53:33,190 --> 00:53:35,060
And thank you...

834
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:44,780
If I knew you're gonna end up crying like this...

835
00:53:45,380 --> 00:53:47,000
I wouldn't tell you the whole story.

836
00:53:47,640 --> 00:53:48,990
How can you not?

837
00:53:49,140 --> 00:53:50,440
This is big.

838
00:53:51,750 --> 00:53:54,550
Bigger than my story is you crying right now.

839
00:54:00,250 --> 00:54:02,740
Why are you so good to me and love me this much?

840
00:54:03,390 --> 00:54:04,910
It's been too long.

841
00:54:05,240 --> 00:54:07,280
You must be in so much pain.

842
00:54:07,820 --> 00:54:09,920
Not as bad as seeing you cry now.

843
00:54:11,500 --> 00:54:12,760
Forget it.

844
00:54:13,150 --> 00:54:15,000
Stop crying.

845
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:19,750
Ok. I will.

846
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:26,310
That's good...

847
00:54:26,760 --> 00:54:28,780
that I didn't go to America.

848
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,220
If I went to America,

849
00:54:32,750 --> 00:54:34,840
I don't know how everything's gonna turn out.

850
00:54:35,020 --> 00:54:37,280
I'm just gonna go to the US more often.
That's all.

851
00:54:41,930 --> 00:54:43,600
Thank you so so much.

852
00:54:44,610 --> 00:54:46,270
Thank you for waiting for so long.

853
00:54:48,150 --> 00:54:50,080
Thank you for never moving on from me.

854
00:54:51,410 --> 00:54:52,930
I love you, P'

855
00:54:54,210 --> 00:54:55,670
I love you so much,

856
00:54:57,970 --> 00:54:59,850
I love you too, North.

857
00:55:14,660 --> 00:55:15,850
North.

858
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:19,130
You don't have to call my name anymore.

859
00:55:19,570 --> 00:55:21,580
If not by your name then what?

860
00:55:21,740 --> 00:55:22,630
Babe?

861
00:55:22,670 --> 00:55:23,610
Hey!

862
00:55:24,260 --> 00:55:26,600
- Babe~
- No.

863
00:55:30,450 --> 00:55:33,850
But I actually don't know what to do either...

864
00:55:34,190 --> 00:55:36,950
I always take from you.

865
00:55:37,630 --> 00:55:39,260
That's not true.

866
00:55:39,620 --> 00:55:41,560
You make me want to change myself.

867
00:55:42,520 --> 00:55:43,660
You are my inspiration.

868
00:55:43,870 --> 00:55:45,410
and you are also my happiness.

869
00:55:47,800 --> 00:55:49,350
Even you said so...

870
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:51,560
You don't have to do anything.

871
00:55:52,360 --> 00:55:53,960
Just being here by my side...

872
00:55:55,210 --> 00:55:57,010
forever like this, can you?

873
00:56:00,830 --> 00:56:02,350
I promise...

874
00:56:02,510 --> 00:56:03,880
...that I won't go anywhere.

875
00:56:04,700 --> 00:56:06,750
I promise you everything.

876
00:56:37,150 --> 00:56:38,440
Stop crying.

877
00:56:50,440 --> 00:56:52,410
My mom invites you to visits my home.

878
00:56:52,480 --> 00:56:53,830
Shall we go to my place too?

879
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:57,880
I have a present for you.

880
00:56:57,950 --> 00:56:59,890
Give this to someone you love.

881
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:01,220
This is for you, Ter.

882
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:03,020
Both shooting stars and the moon.

883
00:57:03,160 --> 00:57:06,840
Just only you by my side, no matter what’s gonna happen in the future.

884
00:57:07,080 --> 00:57:09,600
Surprise!

